#include 'template.wml'

<points>
<li>
The "Oilify" tool enables one to turn a photograph (or something similar)
into an oil painting-like image.
</li>
</points>


<table class="mydemo">
<tr class="mydemo">
<td class="mydemo">

<h3>Demo</h3>

<ol>

<li>
Open g_anwar1.jpg
</li>

<li>
Select
<menupath>
<tt>
&lt;Image&gt; -&gt; Filters -&gt; Artistic -&gt; "Oilify..."
</tt>
</menupath>
</li>

<li>
Select a mask size and press the OK Button.
</li>

<li>
Undo and Play with the various settings.
</li>

</ol>

</td>
</tr>
</table>

<points>
<li>
Oilify works by replacing the pixel at (x,y) with the value that occurs
most often in its N x N neighbourhood.
</li>
<li>
It does so separately for each RGB Channel.
</li>
</points>

